parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, slow down, or come to a complete stop, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or acceleration
the transmission makes a loud whining noise
the vehicle slows down or comes to a complete stop
the transmission goes into limp mode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The faulty sensor can cause the airbag system to malfunction, leading to the deactivation of the passenger airbag, which can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: the passenger airbag off indicator is displayed
and the passenger seat sensor is faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: and the airbags do not deploy in the event of an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of replacement parts, such as the passenger seat, can leave the vehicle in an unsafe condition, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger seat needs to be replaced
but the part is no longer available
and the airbag system is faulty.
